Each of the following packages were either installed from sunfreeware.com (sfw)
or from source obtained from the respective maintainer's site (src).  The order
in which the packages are listed is the order in which they were installed.

Packages:
- binutils	  2.21	(sfw)
- cairo		 1.4.0	(sfw)
- coreutils	  8.11	(sfw)
- doxygen	1.7.4	(sfw)
- expat		 2.0.1	(sfw)
- gawk		 3.1.8	(sfw)
- git		 1.7.5	(sfw)
- libiconv	1.13.1	(sfw)
- libgcrypt	 1.2.4	(sfw)
- openssl	1.0.0d	(sfw)
- gcc		 3.4.6	(sfw)
- libint	 3.4.0	(sfw)
- libsigsegv	  2.10	(sfw)
- libxml2	 2.7.7	(sfw)
- libxslt	1.1.26	(sfw)
- ncurses	   5.7	(sfw)
- gmp		 4.2.1	(sfw)
- xerces-c	 3.1.1	(src)
- axl            0.6.4	(src)
- vortex	1.1.11	(src)
- santuario	 1.6.1	(src)
- test-dept	0.14.2	(src)
- scons		 2.0.1	(sfw)
- libconfig	 1.4.7	(src)
- xqilla	 2.2.4  (src)
- dbxml		2.5.16	(src)
- xmlsec1	1.2.18	(src)

Notes:

The following are notes on what was required in order to build and install the
source packages.

    A number of applications require gcc 3.4.6.

    xerces:
	http://xerces.apache.org/xerces-c/download.cgi

	$ ./configure LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib"
	$ make
	$ make install

    axl:
        http://sourceforge.net/projects/vortexlibrary/files/
        
	In src/axl_log.c, getpid() must be casted as an int.  A patch has been
	supplied.

	$ ./configure CFLAGS="__EXTENSIONS__ -L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib"
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install

    vortex:
        http://sourceforge.net/projects/vortexlibrary/files/

	getpid() must be cast as int in the following files:
		- src/vortex.c
		- test/vortex-simple-listener.c
		- test/vortex-listener.c
		- test/vortex-omr-server.c
		- test/vortex-regression-listener.c
		- test/vortex-file-transfer-server.c	

	export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/usr/local/lib/pkgconfig"
        $ ./configure CFLAGS="-lncurses -lsocket -D__EXTENSIONS__ -I/usr/local/ssl/include \
	-L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib -L/usr/local/ssl/lib \
	-R/usr/local/ssl/lib" PKG_CONFIG_PATH=/usr/local/lib/pkgconfig \
	--disable-py-vortex
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install

    santuario:
	http://santuario.apache.org/download.html

        $ ./configure LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/ssl/lib -R/usr/local/ssl/lib" PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/usr/local/ssl/lib/pkgconfig"
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install

    libconfig:
        http://www.hyperrealm.com/libconfig/

	$ ./configure LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib"
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install

    test-dept:
	$ ./configure
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install

    scons:
	Must be using pythong 2.4.6 in /usr/bin/python
	
	$ python setup.py install

    xqilla:
	http://sourceforge.net/projects/xqilla/files/

	$ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib"
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install

    dbxml:
	http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/database/berkeleydb/downloads/index.html

	The included versions of XQilla and xerces-c were removed from the package
	and the build script was pointed to the local installations of those
	packages.

	$ ./buildall.sh --prefix=/usr/local --build-one=berkeleydb \
	--with-configure-env="LDFLAGS='-L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib'"
	$ ./buildall.sh --prefix=/usr/local --build-one=dbxml \
	--with-xqilla-prefix=/usr/local \
	--with-xerces-prefix=/usr/local \
	--with-berkeleydb-prefix=/usr/local \
	--with-configure-env="LDFLAGS='-L/usr/local/lib -R/usr/local/lib'"

    xmlsec1:
	$ ./configure --with-openssl=/usr/local/ssl
	$ gmake
	$ gmake install
